E ELGIN COUNTY PUBLIC LIBRARY SYSTEM.     THE ELGIN COUNTY (ONTARIO) LIBRARY ASSOCIATION WAS FOUNDED IN 1936; IT WAS ACOOPERATIVE VENTURE AND BY 1964 IT HAD 12 MEMBER LIBRARIES. THESE WEREINDEPENDENT LIBRARIES AND MOST HAD SOMEWHAT PRECARIOUS FINANCIAL SUPPORT FROMTHE COUNTY COUNCIL, LOCAL COUNCIL, AND INTERESTED INDIVIDUALS ANDORGANISATIONS. IN 1964, A FULLY TAX SUPPORTED COUNTY PUBLIC LIBRARY WASSUGGESTED TO REPLACE THE ASSOCIATION. THIS WAS AGREED AND THE NEW SYSTEM WASFOUNDED IN 1966. BRIEFLY DESCRIBES THE SYSTEM'S DEVELOPMENT TO DATE,FINANCING, AND PLANS FOR THE FUTURE